# Error handling & async surfaces

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`async-ui.mdc`**, **`accessibility.mdc`**, **`api-layer.mdc`**, **`api-error-routing.mdc`**, **`data-ownership.mdc`**, **`page-layout.mdc`**. Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

Every **data-driven surface** must implement **loading**, **empty**, **error**, and **success** (content ready). Each surface exposes **one derived `status` union** — not boolean spaghetti in JSX.

## Core rules

1. **Never ship a silent blank UI** — skeleton, empty guidance, error recovery, or content.
2. **Pages render `status`** — they do not combine five TanStack flags inline.

| Layer | Owns |
| ----- | ---- |
| TanStack Query / mutations | Raw fetch/mutation flags |
| Feature hook or `getXxxStatus()` | **Single `status` union** per surface |
| Page / component | `switch (status)` or status-driven subcomponents |

## Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// Bad
if (!data) return null;
if (!data) return <p>No data</p>;

// Good — explicit branches
const { data, isPending, isError, refetch, isFetching } = useItems();
const status = getItemListStatus({ isPending, isError, data });

switch (status) {
  case "loading": return <ItemsSkeleton />;
  case "error": return <ItemsError onRetry={() => void refetch()} />;
  case "empty": return <ItemsEmpty />;
  case "ready": return <ItemTable rows={data!} isRefreshing={isFetching} />;
}
```

## Status unions

### Read surfaces

```typescript
// src/lib/items/itemListStatus.ts
export type ItemListStatus = "loading" | "error" | "empty" | "ready";

export function getItemListStatus({ isPending, isError, data }: {
  isPending: boolean; isError: boolean; data: Item[] | undefined;
}): ItemListStatus {
  if (isPending) return "loading";
  if (isError) return "error";
  if (!data?.length) return "empty";
  return "ready";
}
```

Prefer `ready` over `success` for populated reads; reserve `success` for completed **actions**.

### Write surfaces

```typescript
export type SubmitStatus = "idle" | "submitting" | "success" | "error";
```

One `submitStatus` — not parallel `isSaving`, `isUpdating`, `isSubmitting`. Reset `success` → `idle` after toast/navigation when needed.

### Optional: `thinking` (streaming / AI)

Extend union only where product has visible in-progress cognition: `"idle" | "thinking" | "streaming" | "error"`.

### Multiple regions

Each **region** gets its own status — not one global boolean:

```tsx
<ItemsSummary status={summaryStatus} />
<ActivityPanel status={activityStatus} />
```

### Background refresh

`isFetching` while `status === "ready"` → pass `isRefreshing` as prop, not a conflicting status.

**Do not** derive status in JSX with compound conditions. Unit-test `getXxxStatus` table-driven (`vitest-testing.mdc`).

## State matrix (what to show)

| State | When | UI |
| ----- | ---- | -- |
| **Loading** | Initial fetch (`isPending`) | Skeleton matching final layout |
| **Error** | `isError` | What happened + retry |
| **Empty** | Success + zero items | Teach + primary action |
| **Success** | Data present | Content; subtle `isFetching` for background refetch |

**Empty ≠ error ≠ loading.** Never use the same copy for all three.

## TanStack Query conventions

**Destructure at the call site** before branching — see **`api-layer.mdc`**.

- **`isPending`** — no data yet → skeleton.
- **`isError`** — recovery UI; use `error` for copy when useful.
- **`isFetching` + cached data** — keep content; inline refresh (`async-ui.mdc`).
- **Do not** clear list to `[]` on every refetch unless product requires it.

## Errors: what to show

Every error answers (`copy/ui-microcopy.mdc`):

1. **What happened?** — plain language
2. **Why?** — when it helps (offline, permissions)
3. **What now?** — retry, go back, edit input

API mutation errors: non-validation → toast + rollback in query hooks. Validation → `fieldErrors` in form; no toast.

## Generating & in-progress

Long-running work needs **visible progress** + **`role="status"` / `aria-live="polite"`**. Toasts may supplement — not alone (`accessibility.mdc`).

## Empty states

Never bare “No data”. Include what this is, why empty, primary action. Optional warmth on milestones → **`delight-ux.mdc`** — teach first.

## Partial / multi-region pages

Do not gate the **entire page** on the slowest query. Each region owns its states (`interaction-polish.mdc`).

## Accessibility

- Loading: `aria-busy="true"` when appropriate.
- Errors: visible text + retry; `role="alert"` for critical inline errors.
- Do not rely on color alone.

## Checklist

- [ ] Query/mutation hooks **destructured** at call site (`api-layer.mdc`).
- [ ] One read `status` union per data surface; one `submitStatus` per write flow.
- [ ] No `if (!data) return null` on user-facing surfaces.
- [ ] Loading uses skeleton; empty teaches; error offers retry.
- [ ] Multi-query pages handle each region independently.
- [ ] `empty` / `error` / `loading` / `ready` mutually exclusive for reads.
